cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel method for prototype-based learning that focuses on interpretability and discriminative representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method is evaluated on benchmarks from different domains, including computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which further supports the possibility of these sub-categories. Additionally, the method involves learning a combined embedding in the feature space, which suggests the possibility of neural networks (cs.NE) being involved.
